// ────────────── Startup Applications ──────────────
// Nothing is spawned here. niri runs as `niri.service` and BindsTo
// graphical-session.target, so startup apps are managed by systemd instead
// of spawn-at-startup (see https://github.com/YaLTeR/niri/wiki/Example-systemd-Setup).
//
// Already covered, so intentionally NOT spawned here:
//   swaync       -> swaync.service, enabled (graphical-session.target.wants)
//   nm-applet    -> app-nm\x2dapplet@autostart.service (xdg-autostart generator)
//   warp-taskbar -> app-com.cloudflare.WarpTaskbar@autostart.service (xdg-autostart)
//   xdg-desktop-portal-gnome -> D-Bus activated on demand
//   waybar       -> waybar.service (graphical-session.target.wants)
//
// To add a new startup app:
//   - has a packaged unit:  systemctl --user add-wants niri.service <name>.service
//   - no unit: drop a custom unit in ~/.config/systemd/user/ with
//       [Unit] PartOf=graphical-session.target / After=graphical-session.target
//       [Install] WantedBy=graphical-session.target   then enable it.
